<include>context/python_preamble.prompt</include>

% Goal
Write the `pdd/agentic_sync_runner.py` module.

% Role & Scope
Parallel sync engine that runs `pdd sync` for multiple modules concurrently using a ThreadPoolExecutor, respecting dependency ordering. Posts live progress updates to a GitHub issue comment. On failure, pauses execution (running modules finish, no new ones start).

% Requirements
1. Class: `AsyncSyncRunner(basenames, dep_graph, sync_options, github_info, quiet, verbose)`
   - `basenames: List[str]` — modules to sync
   - `dep_graph: Dict[str, List[str]]` — basename -> [dependency basenames]
   - `sync_options: Dict` — budget, skip_verify, skip_tests, agentic, no_steer, max_attempts, one_session
   - `github_info: Optional[Dict]` — owner, repo, issue_number, cwd (None to disable comments)
   - Tracks per-module state: pending -> running -> success | failed
2. Method: `run() -> Tuple[bool, str, float]` — returns (all_success, summary_message, total_cost)
3. Use `concurrent.futures.ThreadPoolExecutor` with `MAX_WORKERS = 4`
4. Dependency-aware scheduling: a module starts only when all its dependencies (within target set) have status "success"
5. Dependencies NOT in basenames are assumed already synced
6. Pause-on-failure: when any module fails, set `self.failed = True`; let running modules finish but don't start new ones
7. Each module runs as a `pdd sync` subprocess with `--force`, `--agentic`, `--no-steer` flags; append `--one-session` if `sync_options["one_session"]` is truthy
8. Use `PDD_OUTPUT_COST_PATH` env var for cost capture from subprocess (CSV format)
9. Sync failure detection: exit code != 0 OR "Overall status:" line contains "Failed"
10. Per-module timeout: `MODULE_TIMEOUT = 900` seconds (15 minutes)

% Dataclass: `ModuleState`
- `status: str` — "pending", "running", "success", "failed"
- `start_time: Optional[float]`
- `end_time: Optional[float]`
- `cost: float`
- `error: Optional[str]`

% GitHub Comment Updates
- Create comment on first update (`gh api POST`), store `comment_id`
- Subsequent updates: PATCH existing comment
- Markdown table format: Module | Status | Duration | Cost
- Status icons: pending (hourglass), running (sync), success (checkmark), failed (cross)
- Footer: total cost, overall status (in progress / paused / all success)

% Function: `build_dep_graph_from_architecture(arch_path: Path, target_basenames: List[str]) -> Dict[str, List[str]]`
- Load architecture.json, map prompt filename -> basename via `extract_module_from_include`
- Build subgraph: only include dependencies within target_basenames
- Exclude self-dependencies
- Return empty deps for basenames not found in architecture.json

% Helper Functions
- `_find_pdd_executable() -> Optional[str]`: find pdd binary (same pattern as `server/jobs.py`)
- `_parse_cost_from_csv(csv_path: str) -> float`: sum cost column from PDD_OUTPUT_COST_PATH CSV
- `_format_duration(start, end) -> str`: format seconds as "Xs" or "Xm Ys"

% Dependencies
<pdd.agentic_change><include>context/agentic_change_example.py</include></pdd.agentic_change>
<pdd.sync_order><include>context/sync_order_example.py</include></pdd.sync_order>

% Instructions
- Use `threading.Lock` for thread-safe state updates
- Reuse `_run_gh_command` from `agentic_change.py` for GitHub comment API calls
- Set subprocess env: `CI=1`, `PDD_FORCE=1`, `TERM=dumb` for headless execution
- Fallback to `sys.executable -m pdd` if `_find_pdd_executable()` returns None

% Deliverables
- Code: `pdd/agentic_sync_runner.py`
